.TH "fcoe_ctlr_send_keep_alive" 9 "fcoe_ctlr_send_keep_alive" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fcoe_ctlr_send_keep_alive \- Send a keep-alive to the selected FCF
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" fcoe_ctlr_send_keep_alive
.BI "(struct fcoe_ctlr *fip "  ","
.BI "struct fc_lport *lport "  ","
.BI "int ports "  ","
.BI "u8 *sa "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fip" 12
The FCoE controller to send the FKA on
.IP "lport" 12
libfc fc_lport to send from
.IP "ports" 12
0 for controller keep-alive, 1 for port keep-alive
.IP "sa" 12
The source MAC address
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
A controller keep-alive is sent every fka_period (typically 8 seconds).
The source MAC is the native MAC address.

A port keep-alive is sent every 90 seconds while logged in.
The source MAC is the assigned mapped source address.
The destination is the FCF's F-port.
